<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1673,2021]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1781,1805]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[321,545,1781,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Pyralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penkleriana">
<emphasis box="[321,545,1781,1805]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Pyralis penkleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is based on material in Schiffermüller’s collection, but 
<bibRefCitation author="Fabricius" box="[1181,1368,1781,1805]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1787) Mantissa insectorvm sistens eorum species nvper detectas adiectics characteribvs genericis, differentiis, specificis, emendationibvs, observationibvs. Tom [us] I, Hafniae, i - xx, 348 pp." type="book" year="1787">
Fabricius (
<number box="[1302,1361,1781,1805]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1787.0">1787</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
gives no literal reference to 
<taxonomicName authority="Denis and Schiffermuller, 1775" authorityName="Denis and Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1775" box="[405,978,1817,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Tinea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penkleriana">
<emphasis box="[405,610,1817,1841]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tinea penkleriana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Denis" box="[619,978,1817,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Denis, M. &amp; Schiffermuller, I. (1775) Ankundung eines systematisches Werkes von den Schemetterlinge der Wiener Gegend herausgegeben von einigen Lehrern am k. k. Theresianum. Wien, Austria, i + 323 pp, 3 pls." type="book" year="1775">
Denis and Schiffermüller, 
<number box="[919,978,1817,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Herrich-Schaffer" box="[991,1299,1817,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Herrich-Schaffer, G. A. W. (1856) Index alphabetico-synonymicus ad Vol. I - V. Pp. (1) 24, (2) 64, (3) 34, (4) 48, (5) 52. Systematische Bearbeitung der Schmetterlinge von Europa, 6. Regensburg." type="journal article" year="1856">
Herrich-Schäffer (
<number box="[1197,1254,1817,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1856.0">1856</number>
(
<number box="[1272,1289,1817,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="4.0">4</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number box="[1312,1341,1817,1841]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="32.0">32</number>
) associated the name with 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke" authorityName="Treitschke" box="[373,791,1853,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gypsonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oppressana">
<emphasis box="[373,643,1854,1877]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Gypsonoma oppressana</emphasis>
(Treitschke)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Werneburg" box="[801,1007,1853,1877]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Werneburg, A. (1864) Beitrage zur Schmetterlingskunde. Part 1, Erfurt, Verlag von H. Neumann, 595 pp." type="book" year="1864">
Werneburg (
<number box="[940,999,1853,1877]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1864.0">1864</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymised the species with 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner. However" authorityName="Hubner. However" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Tortrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aspidiscana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Tortrix aspidiscana</emphasis>
Hübner. However
</taxonomicName>
, the association of the name with Denis and Schiffermüller persisted in the older literature. This must be the origin of many misidentifications as the identity of 
<taxonomicName box="[1003,1137,1925,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Tinea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penkleriana">
<emphasis box="[1003,1137,1925,1949]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">penkleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D. and S. has been controversial. However, as pointed out by Karsholt (
<emphasis box="[666,688,1962,1985]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">in</emphasis>
Razowski 
<number box="[811,871,1961,1985]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1996.0">1996</number>
), Fischer von 
<bibRefCitation author="Roslerstamm" box="[1028,1314,1961,1985]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" refString="Fischer von Roslerstamm, J. E. (1840) Abbildungen zur Berichtigung un Erganzung der Schmetterlingskunde besonders der Microlepidoptereologie als supplement zu Treitschke's und Huebner's europaeischen Schmetterlingen, mit Erlaeuterndem Text. Part 14: 189 - 200, pls. 66 - 70. J. C. Hinrich'schen Buchhandlung, Leipzig, Germany." type="book chapter" year="1840">
Röslerstamm (
<number box="[1192,1253,1961,1985]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1840.0">1840</number>
: 
<number box="[1263,1306,1961,1985]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="198.0">198</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[304,438,1997,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Tinea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penkleriana">
<emphasis box="[304,438,1997,2021]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">penkleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Schiffermüller's collection belong to the species currently known as 
<taxonomicName authority="Denis and Schiffermuller, 1775" authorityName="Denis and Schiffermuller" authorityYear="1775" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Epinotia" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenerana">
<emphasis box="[1233,1435,1998,2021]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Epinotia tenerana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Denis" box="[158,515,151,175]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Denis, M. &amp; Schiffermuller, I. (1775) Ankundung eines systematisches Werkes von den Schemetterlinge der Wiener Gegend herausgegeben von einigen Lehrern am k. k. Theresianum. Wien, Austria, i + 323 pp, 3 pls." type="book" year="1775">
Denis and Schiffermüller, 
<number box="[456,515,151,175]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1775.0">1775</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and many authors treat the name in this sense. Among them are widely used references such as 
<bibRefCitation author="Kennel" box="[334,491,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Kennel, J. von (1910) Tortricidae. In: Spuler, A. (Ed), Die Schmetterlinge Europas. Kleinschmetterlinge. Schweizerbart'sche Verlagsbuchhandlung, Stuttgart, Germany, pp 238 - 296." type="book chapter" year="1910">
Kennel (
<number box="[431,491,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1910.1921">1910</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1921), 
<bibRefCitation author="Meyrick" box="[584,763,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Meyrick, E. (1895) A Handbook of British Lepidoptera. McMillan and Co., London, U. K., 843 pp." type="book" year="1895">
Meyrick (
<number box="[695,755,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1895.0">1895</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Rebel" box="[824,976,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Rebel, H. 1901. In Staudinger, O. &amp; Rebel, H. Catalog der Lepidopteren des palaearctischen Faunengebietes, 2. R. Friedlander &amp; Sohn, Berlin, Germany, 368 pp." type="book" year="1901">
Rebel (
<number box="[906,966,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1901.0">1901</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Another group of authors, derived from 
<bibRefCitation author="Hubner" box="[151,316,223,247]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Hubner, J. (1825) Catalogue des Lepidopteres qui composent la collection de fue Mr. Frank. Strassburg, France, 102 pp." type="book" year="1825">
Hübner (
<number box="[250,308,223,247]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1825.0">1825</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
associate this name with 
<taxonomicName authority="Treitschke. Finally, Beccaloni et al. (2005)" authorityName="Treitschke. Finally, Beccaloni et al." authorityYear="2005" box="[603,1263,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phiaris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olivana">
<emphasis box="[603,776,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Phiaris olivana</emphasis>
Treitschke. Finally, 
<bibRefCitation box="[1005,1263,223,248]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Beccaloni, G., Scoble, M. J., Robinson, G. &amp; Pitkin, B. (Eds) (2005) The Global Lepidoptera Names Index (LepIndex). Natural History Museum London. Available from: http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / research-curation / research / projects / lepindex / (accessed: May 2011)." type="book chapter">
Beccaloni 
<emphasis box="[1124,1180,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[1194,1255,223,247]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2005.0">2005</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, strongly influenced by 
<bibRefCitation author="Obraztsov" box="[259,458,260,284]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" refString="Obraztsov, N. S. (1959) Die Gattungen der Palaearktischen Tortricidae II. Unterfamilie Olethreutinae, 2. Teil. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 102 (2), 175 - 216, pl. 23 - 26." type="journal article" year="1959">
Obraztsov (
<number box="[390,450,260,284]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1959.0">1959</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, associate 
<taxonomicName box="[579,713,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Tinea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penkleriana">
<emphasis box="[579,713,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">penkleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner, 1796" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1796" box="[778,1149,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendana">
<emphasis box="[778,967,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Cydia splendana</emphasis>
(Hübner, 
<number box="[1081,1141,260,284]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1796.0">1796</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Because 
<taxonomicName box="[1261,1410,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendana">
<emphasis box="[1261,1410,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">C. splendana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an economically important pest on 
<taxonomicName box="[544,651,296,320]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fagaceae</taxonomicName>
, the name is well established in the literature. Brown (
<number box="[1256,1315,295,319]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2005.0">2005</number>
) prefers to conserve 
<taxonomicName box="[260,375,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cydia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendana">
<emphasis box="[260,375,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">splendana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and questions the use of 
<taxonomicName box="[670,803,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Tinea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penkleriana">
<emphasis box="[670,803,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">penkleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D. and S. as a synonym. Today, the correct identity of 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius" authorityName="Fabricius" box="[151,512,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Pyralidae" genus="Pyralis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penkleriana">
<emphasis box="[151,377,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Pyralis penkleriana</emphasis>
(Fabricius)
</taxonomicName>
cannot be proved. However, we find that it serves stability best to follow the authors who treat it as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName box="[564,802,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Epinotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="penkleriana">
<emphasis box="[564,802,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Epinotia penkleriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(D. and S.) and of 
<taxonomicName box="[1016,1146,405,428]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Epinotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenerana">
<emphasis box="[1016,1146,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">E. tenerana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(D. and S.).
</paragraph>
